Now I have a thorough understanding of the current review system. Let me create the design document.
Created `docs/design/automation-review-management.md` (349 lines). The document covers 7 automation areas:

1. **Auto-trigger review on app open** — redirect to /review when 5+ items are overdue and user was away >24h
2. **Smart notification scheduling** — dynamic reminder timing based on review load, graduated urgency escalation, push notification support
3. **Unified pending review dashboard** — `CombinedReviewService` aggregates 6 review types with priority scoring (overdue ×10 + low-rep penalty + exam proximity boost)
4. **Session resumption** — checkpoint saved on each card rating, `beforeunload` handler, resume within 2h window
5. **Adaptive queue sizing** — time-aware queue builder (30s/vocab, 2min/exercise), configurable session length, batch prefetch for large queues
6. **Proactive review badge** — persistent header badge with type breakdown, quick-review sidebar panel, streak tracking
7. **Completion feedback** — performance-based scheduling (auto-tune intervals), optimal next-review-time prediction

